  "text": "FTIR Spectroscopy-Time-resolved FTIR difference spectra were recorded in the rapid scan mode similar to earlier studies [CITATION_1] . Briefly a bR⅐NLP film was dried on a CaF 2 window, rehydrated via the vapor phase, and then sealed in a temperature-controlled IR cell (Model TFC, Harrick Scientific Corp., Ossining, NY) using a second CaF 2 window. Spectra were recorded with a Bruker IFS 66 v/s FTIR spectrometer (Bruker Optics, Ettlingen, Germany) at 4 cm Ϫ1 spectral resolution and 240-kHz scanner velocity, corresponding to the data acquisition window of 18 ms. Four single beam spectra were recorded before the laser flash and were used as the \"dark\" background. A neodymiumdoped yttrium aluminum garnet (Nd/YAG) laser pulse initiated the photocycle, and 80 \"light\" spectra were recorded with each acquisition taking 18 ms. Spectra taken in this sequence were co-added 40,000 times to achieve a high signal-to-noise ratio.",
